codecamp.org/news/content/images/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-3.22.24-AM.png 2162w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px" width="600" height="400" loading="lazy"></figure><p>In this <a href="https://pythonspot.com/beginner/">series of Pythonspot beginner tutorials</a>, you will learn about data types, tuples, objects, classes, dictionaries and more. You will also learn about advanced concepts like recursion, lambda, and threading. </p><p>Once you cover the basics, you can move onto <a href="https://pythonspot.com/machine-learning/">machine learning</a>, <a href="https://pythonspot.com/python-database/">databases</a>, and <a href="https://pythonspot.com/gui/">GUI's</a>. </p><h2 id="python-tutorial">Python Tutorial</h2><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card"><img src="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-3.31.29-AM.png" class="kg-image" alt="Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-3.31.29-AM" srcset="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-3.31.29-AM.png 600w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w1000/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-3.31.29-AM.png 1000w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w1600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-3.31.29-AM.png 1600w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w2400/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-3.31.29-AM.png 2400w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px" width="600" height="400" loading="lazy"></figure><p>In this <a href="https://www.pythonforbeginners.com/python-tutorial">PythonForBeginners tutorial</a>, you will learn about functions, loops, lists, conditionals, error handling and more. &nbsp;</p><p>Once you learn the basics, you can explore the other modules on the site including <a href="https://www.pythonforbeginners.com/python-on-the-web/web-scraping-with-beautifulsoup">Web Scraping with BeautifulSoup</a> and <a href="https://www.pythonforbeginners.com/api/using-the-youtube-api">Using the YouTube API in Python</a>. </p><h2 id="automate-the-boring-stuff-with-python">Automate the Boring Stuff with Python</h2><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card"><img src="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.30.07-AM.png" class="kg-image" alt="Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.30.07-AM" srcset="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.30.07-AM.png 600w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w1000/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.30.07-AM.png 1000w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w1600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.30.07-AM.png 1600w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.30.07-AM.png 1834w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px" width="600" height="400" loading="lazy"></figure><p>In <a href="https://automatetheboringstuff.com/">Automate the Boring Stuff with Python online book</a>, you will learn about dictionaries, strings, debugging, regular expressions and more. </p><p>If you prefer a video format, then you can go through <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1F_OgqRuSdI&amp;list=PL0-84-yl1fUnRuXGFe_F7qSH1LEnn9LkW">the YouTube series </a>that Al Sweigart put together. </p><h2 id="learn-python-2">Learn Python 2</h2><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card"><img src="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.43.41-AM.png" class="kg-image" alt="Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.43.41-AM" srcset="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.43.41-AM.png 600w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w1000/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.43.41-AM.png 1000w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w1600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.43.41-AM.png 1600w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.43.41-AM.png 2378w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px" width="600" height="400" loading="lazy"></figure><p>In this <a href="https://www.codecademy.com/learn/learn-python">Codecademy course</a>, you will learn basic syntax, strings, functions, lists, conditionals and more. This course will also cover more advanced topics like list slicing and lambda expressions. </p><p>In order to take the course you will need to create an account. </p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card"><img src="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.47.24-AM.png" class="kg-image" alt="Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.47.24-AM" srcset="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.47.24-AM.png 600w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w1000/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.47.24-AM.png 1000w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.47.24-AM.png 1156w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px" width="600" height="400" loading="lazy"></figure><h2 id="learn-python-the-hard-way">Learn Python the Hard Way</h2><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card"><img src="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.53.57-AM.png" class="kg-image" alt="Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.53.57-AM" srcset="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.53.57-AM.png 600w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w1000/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.53.57-AM.png 1000w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w1600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.53.57-AM.png 1600w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-2.53.57-AM.png 1840w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px" width="600" height="400" loading="lazy"></figure><p>In <a href="https://learnpythonthehardway.org/book/"></a><a href="https://shop.learncodethehardway.org/access/buy/2/">Learn Python 2 the Hard Way</a>, you will learn about variables, conditionals, functions, classes, objects and more. You will also learn how to build a website and a game. </p><p>You also have the option to do the updated version of the book which is <a href="https://shop.learncodethehardway.org/access/buy/9/">Learn Python 3 the Hard Way</a>. Both of these books are paid options only. &nbsp;</p><h2 id="python-crash-course-for-beginners">Python Crash Course for Beginners</h2><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card"><img src="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-10-at-8.58.23-AM.png" class="kg-image" alt="Screen-Shot-2021-08-10-at-8.58.23-AM" srcset="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-10-at-8.58.23-AM.png 600w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w1000/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-10-at-8.58.23-AM.png 1000w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-10-at-8.58.23-AM.png 1434w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px" width="600" height="400" loading="lazy"></figure><p>In this <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JJmcL1N2KQs">Brad Traversy YouTube course</a>, you will learn about lists, tuples, dictionaries, functions, classes and more. Brad will also show you how to work with files and JSON data. </p><h2 id="python-tutorial-python-for-beginners">Python Tutorial - Python for Beginners </h2><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card"><img src="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-12.06.56-AM.png" class="kg-image" alt="Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-12.06.56-AM" srcset="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-12.06.56-AM.png 600w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w1000/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-12.06.56-AM.png 1000w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-06-at-12.06.56-AM.png 1434w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px" width="600" height="400" loading="lazy"></figure><p>In this <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_uQrJ0TkZlc">Programming with Mosh YouTube course,</a> &nbsp;you will learn programming basics like variables, loops, strings, tuples, functions, classes and more. </p><p>You will also build three projects: one on automation, one on machine learning, and one on building a website with Django. </p><p>For additional practice, you can go through Mosh's <a href="https://programmingwithmosh.com/python/python-exercises-and-questions-for-beginners/">53 Python Exercises for Beginners</a>.</p><h2 id="scientific-computing-with-python">Scientific Computing with Python</h2><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card"><img src="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-10-at-9.06.10-AM.png" class="kg-image" alt="Screen-Shot-2021-08-10-at-9.06.10-AM" srcset="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-10-at-9.06.10-AM.png 600w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w1000/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-10-at-9.06.10-AM.png 1000w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/size/w1600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-10-at-9.06.10-AM.png 1600w, https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/content/images/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-10-at-9.06.10-AM.png 1622w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px" width="600" height="400" loading="lazy"></figure><p>In <a href="https://www.freecodecamp.org/learn/scientific-computing-with-python/">this freeCodeCamp certification course</a>, you will learn about loops, lists, dictionaries, networking, web services and more. </p><p>You will also have the opportunity to build five projects: <a href="https://www.freecodecamp.org/learn/scientific-computing-with-python/scientific-computing-with-python-projects/arithmetic-formatter">Arithmetic Formatter</a>, <a href="https://www.freecodecamp.org/learn/scientific-computing-with-python/scientific-computing-with-python-projects/time-calculator">Time Calculator,</a> <a href="https://www.freecodecamp.org/learn/scientific-computing-with-python/scientific-computing-with-python-projects/budget-app">Budget App,</a> <a href="https://www.freecodecamp.org/learn/scientific-computing-with-python/scientific-computing-with-python-projects/polygon-area-calculator">Polygon Area Calculator</a>, and <a href="https://www.freecodecamp.org/learn/scientific-computing-with-python/scientific-computing-with-python-projects/probability-calculator">Probability Calculator</a>. <br></p>

                        </section>
                        
